The paper focuses on analyzing and supporting the adaptation of online code examples, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of automated adaptation analysis techniques and a Chrome extension, which could fall under programming languages (cs.PL) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories. The dataset construction and analysis techniques used in the paper could also fall under the cybernetics (cs.CY) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
